So as much as i like to give back unfortunately  theres is a limit to what i and most of my fellow canadians can contribute.  Infact the CRTC just passed a new law circumventing any CND ISP from offering unlimited bandwidth by allowing pay per use legislature basically allowing ISP's to charge per page.  Goodbye Internet as we know it.  Just like radio and TV.  Radio was too hard too charge because of the basic tech.  but with tv it was free when it first came out as long as you owned a tv set.  looks like the wwweb is headed in the same direction.,  So to make it short please consider that some of us have our hands or Bands (depends how you look at it.lol) tied. pirate on! to infinite and beyond!
